Introduction

TOZ is a Japanese boy group based in South Korea. The group was formed by YY Entertainment and consists of four members: Anthonny, Hart, Yuto, and Takuto. They debuted on September 27, 2023, with the mini-album "Flare".

The name "TOZ" is an acronym of the words "To Our Zone".

The group members were already well-known before their debut due to their participation in survival shows. All the members are former contestants on "Boys Planet". Anthonny is also a former "Produce 101 Japan Season 2" contestants and Hart was a contestant on "LOUD".

On October 27, 2023, TOZ announced their fandom name "TOPAZ" which means "Beautiful and Precious like the gem, TOPAZ".

On May 2, 2024, TOZ made their official Korean debut with the mini album "TO my new friends". They previously released the Korean version of "Magic Hour" on March 14.
